  "text": "Audit CSP enforcement in Firefox. The XPCOM interface is defined in dom/interfaces/security/nsIContentSecurityPolicy.idl. CSP policy parsing is handled by nsCSPParser (dom/security/nsCSPParser.h/.cpp) which tokenizes and validates CSP directives including script-src for inline script evaluation. The central enforcement context is nsCSPContext (dom/security/nsCSPContext.h/.cpp) which implements nsIContentSecurityPolicy and performs ShouldLoad checks against all registered policies. CSP utility classes for directive representation and matching live in nsCSPUtils (dom/security/nsCSPUtils.h/.cpp). The content policy integration point is nsCSPService (dom/security/nsCSPService.h/.cpp). Violation reporting is handled through CSPViolationData (dom/security/CSPViolationData.h/.cpp) which structures violation events per the W3C spec. Policy containers (dom/security/PolicyContainer.cpp) serialize/deserialize CSP for IPC.",
  "_metadata": {
